  "body": "**Problem:** \r\n\r\nWhile running remixd command to give permission to remix to access my local directory: \r\n\r\n`remixd -s /Users/nikolamadjarevic/Desktop/2key.network/contracts/contracts --remix-ide http://remix.ethereum.org` I see that now, even this command is given, remixd opens access to my whole harddrive.\r\n\r\n![Screenshot 2021-02-09 at 11 20 49](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30060076/107349741-ddac6b80-6ac8-11eb-8e27-5b21a5b949dc.png)\r\n\r\nWhen I connect using plugins in remix, this is the log I'm getting on the console: \r\n```\r\nsetup notifications for /Users/nikolamadjarevic/Desktop/2key.network/contracts/contracts\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is what remix loads: \r\n<img width=\"308\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-02-09 at 11 22 19\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30060076/107349916-15b3ae80-6ac9-11eb-98f3-1f0173d177bb.png\">\r\n\r\n### Reporting here 2 issues: \r\n- Remix behavior --> Can't load the directory I specified\r\n- Remixd actually has access to the whole harddrive. \r\n\r\n**Env:** \r\n- Mac OS Big Sur\r\n- Node: v10.23.0\r\n- Npm: 6.14.8\r\n\r\n",
